## Order-Signifigant Documents

The most powerful document decoders are these, which preserve the order of
the nodes which they parse rather than forming them into a more ergonomic
datastructure.  This means that you can arrange the nodes into your own
order-aware datastructure, although it forces you to do a little bit more work.

@docs document
@docs documentF

# Error Handling

Sometimes, users or programmers make mistakes, and produce a KDL document which
is valid KDL, but still contains mistakes that make it un-decodeable.  When this
happens, it's important to provide helpful and specific error messages so that
the problem can be quickly identified and resolved.  This module contains some
error handling tools which aim to make this proccess simpler.

